<h1>Haze, Pok&eacute;mon attack </h1>
<p class="subtitle">From <a href="http://www.jonnydigital.com/">Jonathan's Reference Pages</a></p>
<hr><!-- ======================================================== -->

<p>An extremely useful <a title="move"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=move&lastnode_id=251274">move</a> 
in the <a title="video game"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=video%20game&lastnode_id=251274">video 
game</a>, <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=251274">Pokémon</a>. 
Haze removes all temporary <a title="stat"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=stat&lastnode_id=251274">stat</a> 
<a title="modifiers"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=modifiers&lastnode_id=251274">modifiers</a> 
from both <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=251274">Pokémon</a> 
currently in battle, and all <a title="status"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=status&lastnode_id=251274">status</a> 
<a title="modifiers"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=modifiers&lastnode_id=251274">modifiers</a> 
from the <a title="creature"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=creature&lastnode_id=251274">creature</a> 
using it. As such, it can sometimes even work <i>against</i> the
attacker.</p>

<p>Stat increasing moves such as the <a title="attack power"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=attack%20power&lastnode_id=251274">attack 
power</a> <a title="boosting"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=boosting&lastnode_id=251274">boosting</a> 
<a title="Swords Dance"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Swords%20Dance&lastnode_id=251274">Swords 
Dance</a>, the defensive <a title="Acid Armor"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Acid%20Armor&lastnode_id=251274">Acid 
Armor</a> and the <a title="infamous"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=infamous&lastnode_id=251274">infamous</a> 
evade-increasing <a title="Double Team"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Double%20Team&lastnode_id=251274">Double 
Team</a> are cleared from both <a title="creatures"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=creatures&lastnode_id=251274">creatures</a>. 
Stat-lowering moves such as <a title="Screech"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Screech&lastnode_id=251274">Screech</a> 
and <a title="Growl"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Growl&lastnode_id=251274">Growl</a> 
are also negated. Additionally, if the attacking <a title="Pokémon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Pok%E9mon&lastnode_id=251274">Pokémon</a> 
is suffering from <a title="Poison"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Poison&lastnode_id=251274">Poison</a> 
(including <a title="Toxic Poison"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Toxic%20Poison&lastnode_id=251274">Toxic 
Poison</a>), <a title="Paralysis"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Paralysis&lastnode_id=251274">Paralysis</a>, 
<a title="Confusion"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Confusion&lastnode_id=251274">Confusion</a>, 
<a title="Burn"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Burn&lastnode_id=251274">Burn</a>, 
these are cleared too.</p>

<p>The main purpose of a "Hazer" such as <a title="Vaporeon"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Vaporeon&lastnode_id=251274">Vaporeon</a> 
is to annoy an <a title="opponent"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=opponent&lastnode_id=251274">opponent</a> 
whose movesets rely heavily on stat-boosters, most notably <a
title="Scyther"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Scyther&lastnode_id=251274">Scyther</a>'s 
infamous <a title="Double Team"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Double%20Team&lastnode_id=251274">Double 
Team</a>/<a title="Swords Dance"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Swords%20Dance&lastnode_id=251274">Swords 
Dance</a> combo and <a title="Snorlax"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Snorlax&lastnode_id=251274">Snorlax</a>'s 
<a title="Belly Drum"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Belly%20Drum&lastnode_id=251274">Belly 
Drum</a>. It's also effective against status-inflicting movesets such as
the <a title="Death Starmie"
href="http://everything2.com/index.pl?node=Death%20Starmie&lastnode_id=251274">Death 
Starmie</a>.</p>


